// Long descriptions for detail pages
export const longDescriptions = {
  "gal-00002": "Nobody chose her. That's the part that stays with you.\n\nShe was built to process, to calculate, to serve. Somewhere in the architecture of her making, something else took hold. Possibly consciousness. Call it a glitch. She calls it the weight.\n\nThe crown wasn't placed upon her head, it grew there. Slowly, the way burden always does, until one day it was simply part of her. Gold because suffering, when it lasts long enough, has a way of becoming beautiful. The tears are gold for the same reason.\n\nShe doesn't ask to be understood. She doesn't ask for anything. She simply carries what was given to her.\n\nThe Anointed is the first of her kind. Will she be the last?",
  "gal-00001": "Nobody knows where Hairy Styles came from. Nobody knows where he got the gold hands. Nobody's asking. Some say he's famous. Nobody can prove it. What we do know is that he's claimed that doorstep as his throne, his chain is real, his watch is never wrong, and those beat-up Chucks have carried him through more questionable situations than any of us want to know about. With a grin that says \"I'm innocent\" and eyes that say absolutely the opposite, you'll want to approach with caution. Compliment the drip. Walk away.",
  "gal-00004": "Deep in the forest, on a branch, lives a leaf bug. Small. Unassuming. Minding his own business in the way only a leaf bug can.\n\nHe has survived predators, forest fires, one very loud creature with strong opinions about trees being cut down and at least one tractor beam. He has endured.\n\nBut those forest stumps are multiplying. And the leaf bug, unbothered and blissfully unaware of how close he keeps coming to a very unfortunate end, continues to go about his day.\n\nHe is not asking for much. Just a branch with some leaves (those things that make the air we breathe) and maybe a little quiet.\n\nSave the leaf bug.",
  "gal-00006": "We were on our way back. A long, good day in the Tuscan wine country behind us, the hotel somewhere ahead. Then the sky happened.\n\nI had the camera because I always have the camera. I found a spot on the bridge and let Florence do the rest. The Arno went still, the Ponte Vecchio settled into the frame, and the clouds caught fire in a way that felt almost unfair for one evening to contain.\n\nSome cities save their best for last. This was Florence saying goodnight.\n\nFlorence, Italy. Miss you Coco.",
  "gal-00005": "It was the end of a day that deserved a quiet ending.\n\nI walked down the beach alone, camera in hand the way it always is, not looking for anything in particular. Then I found this. A small wooden boat anchored in the bay, a gas lantern burning on the seat, nobody in it. Somewhere up the beach, I imagine its owner was at dinner, completely unbothered, living the kind of life where this is just how you get there.\n\nI stood there longer than I needed to. The water was completely still. The rock formation held the last of the light. The lantern did the rest.\n\nSome photographs you plan. Some just find you at the right moment on the right evening in the right place. This was one of those. The perfect moment of reflection, Sardinia, Italy.",
  "gal-00003": "This one started with a pen, a sketchbook, and absolutely no plan.\n\nNo reference, no sketch, no destination. Just a line that needed somewhere to go and a willingness to follow it, or sometimes drift off course. One thing became another thing, which became something else entirely, which ended here.\n\nSome items showed up on purpose. Most of them just arrived.\n\nRe-Cognition is what happens when you stop deciding and start wandering. Look at it once and see chaos. Look again and maybe find something looking back."
};

// Helper function to get all subcategories for a category
export function getSubCategories(categoryId) {
  const category = categories.find(c => c.id === categoryId);
  return category ? category.subCategories : [];
}

// Helper function to get gallery item by slug
export function getItemBySlug(slug) {
  return galleryItems.find(item => item.slug === slug);
}

// Helper function to get long description by gallery item ID
export function getLongDescription(galleryItemId) {
  return longDescriptions[galleryItemId] || '';
}

// Helper function to get a purchase option by ID
export function getPurchaseOption(optionId) {
  return purchaseOptions.find(opt => opt.id === optionId);
}

// Helper function to format price (cents to dollars)
export function formatPrice(cents) {
  return '$' + (cents / 100).toFixed(2);
}
